   <mods:abstract>Writes from Nantes. Mrs. Joshua Johnson has been too unwell to execute
            Sarah's commission, but she soon will. She has shown Brockholst a riding suit for Mrs.
            Bingham. "Our affairs must be in a promising train while the ladies can afford such
            extravagance." Brockholst went to the first masquerade he had ever seen. "I wonder any
            lady who has the least pretensions to modesty will be seen at a place where disorder,
            double entendres, and indecency are so prevalent. Perhaps none there labored under this
            embarrassment. It was certainly fortunate for me not to be sufficiently acquainted with
            the language to understand the half of what was said. By this ignorance the delicate
            organs of my hearing escaped and spare me the imputation of modesty, which must often,
            in spite of ever effort, have discovered itself by the blushes which would have
            overspread the cheeks of a much less bashful fellow than myself"</mods:abstract>
